Types of transaction propagation
-------------------------------- 


1️⃣ REQUIRED (Default)

📌 Behavior

Joins the existing transaction if present

Creates a new transaction if none exists

@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRED)
public void saveOrder() {
}


2️⃣ REQUIRES_NEW

📌 Behavior

Suspends the existing transaction

Always creates a new transaction

@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
public void saveAuditLog() {
}


3️⃣ SUPPORTS

📌 Behavior

Uses existing transaction if present

Executes without transaction if none exists

@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.SUPPORTS)
public List<Order> getOrders() {
}


4️⃣ NOT_SUPPORTED

📌 Behavior

Suspends existing transaction

Executes non-transactionally


@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.NOT_SUPPORTED)
public void generateReport() {
}


5️⃣ MANDATORY

📌 Behavior

Must run inside an existing transaction

Throws exception if no transaction exists

@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.MANDATORY)
public void updateAccount() {
}


6️⃣ NEVER

📌 Behavior

Must NOT run inside a transaction

Throws exception if a transaction exists

@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.NEVER)
public void externalCall() {
}


7️⃣ NESTED

📌 Behavior

Runs inside existing transaction

Creates a savepoint

Rolls back only to the savepoint (not full rollback)

@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.NESTED)
public void processItem() {
}


